## Why This Is Asked
Explores runtime policy update, data residency, and per-tenant isolation without redeploying models. 

## Key Concepts
- Runtime policy engine integrated with config store
- Per-tenant data sovereignty and RBAC
- Latency targets and fallback paths

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo: policy fetch & eval before OpenAI call
async function handle(req, tenantId){
  const policies = await fetchPolicy(tenantId);
  if(!evaluate(policies, req)) throw new Error('Policy violation');
  const redacted = redact(req.body);
  return await callOpenAI(redacted);
}
```

